interestingcomments.content: For those interested in serial numbers, I have some sharkskin cameras, all IIc and IIIc with numbers: 438005, 440372, 460149, 460727, 467743, 471173, 488285, 491082, 496949. I also have Leitz binoculars, early post war with sharkskin covering. Maybe benifiting of better grip for these. Every one of these sharkskin cameras is perfect and without shrinkage, suggesting the sharkskin was longer lasting. All seem to be the vertical pattern for mine. I have 135 Hektors with the sharkskin covering, both in chrome and black paint, mostly arround 700xxx.

I have 135 Hektors with the sharkskin covering, both in chrome and black paint, mostly arround 700xxx.
